## Part 1 — PlayerProfileScreen.kt

### Data to load

Load all of this from existing SteamService / Steam Web API. Fetch on screen entry,
show shimmer while loading, never show a blank screen.

```kotlin
data class PlayerProfile(
    val steamId: String,
    val displayName: String,
    val avatarUrl: String,           // full 184px avatar from Steam CDN
    val profileUrl: String,          // e.g. steamcommunity.com/id/username
    val presenceState: PresenceState,// Online / Offline / InGame / Away
    val currentGameName: String?,    // null if not in a game
    val currentGameAppId: Int?,      // used to load game header art
    val currentGameHeaderUrl: String?,// https://cdn.../{appId}/header.jpg
    val statusMessage: String?,      // custom status set by the user
    val memberSince: String?,        // "Member since June 2009"
    val countryCode: String?,        // ISO country code for flag emoji
    val level: Int,                  // Steam level (from GetSteamLevel)
    val levelXpCurrent: Int,         // XP within current level
    val levelXpRequired: Int,        // XP needed for next level
    val totalAchievements: Int,      // across all games
    val totalGames: Int,             // library size
    val recentGames: List<RecentGame>// up to 3 most recent, for profile cards
)

data class RecentGame(
    val appId: Int,
    val name: String,
    val headerUrl: String,
    val playtime2Weeks: Int,         // minutes
    val playtimeForever: Int         // minutes
)
```

